class:: LCOscCh
summary:: LC circuit oscillator and resonator from WaveDigitalFilters
categories:: UGens>Effects
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

LCOscCh follows the `LCOscillator` example from `WaveDigitalFilters`. The model is a discretized LC network, so the oscillation and damping come from the exchange of energy between inductor and capacitor states rather than from a textbook band-limited waveform formula. The `freq` control changes the effective resonance point, and the feedback condition determines whether the network behaves more like a struck resonator, a driven oscillator, or a marginally sustained loop.

Because it is rooted in a resonant circuit model, the tone can feel more physically reactive than a basic sinusoid or saw generator. Short excitations reveal pinged, almost percussive ringing; sustained driving makes the oscillator feel more like a self-energized analog network.

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::in
Input or excitation signal.

argument::freq
Resonant frequency in Hz. Clamped to `20..2000`.

argument::closed
Switch state. Values greater than or equal to `0.5` are treated as closed.

argument::mul
Output multiplier.

argument::add
Output offset.


